D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20CEO%20of%20Ukrainian%20drone%20maker%20Athlon%20Avia%20on%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20facing%20the%20industry%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22781%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Athlon%20Avia%20has%20been%20manufacturing%20drones%20in%20Ukraine%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c1d00eb1834fe31165c663%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22586%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAthlon%20Avia%20has%20been%20manufacturing%20drones%20in%20Ukraine%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%3Cp%3EAthlon%20Avia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUkrainian%20defense%20company%20Athlon%20Avia%20has%20been%20producing%20drones%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20was%20born%20in%202014%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Breaction%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20Russian%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%2C%20its%20CEO%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20chief%20executive%20spoke%20with%20BI%20about%20drones%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20the%20challenges%20facing%20his%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20defense%20company%20Athlon%20Avia%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-says-world-largest-producer-tactical-strategic-drones-war-russia-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproducing%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Ukraine's%20armed%20forces%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtem%20Vyunnyk%2C%20Athlon's%20CEO%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20was%20founded%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Breaction%26quot%3B%20to%20Russia's%20annexation%20of%20Crimea%20and%20the%20outbreak%20of%20the%20Donbas%20war%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20Athlon%20has%20developed%20%26quot%3Bvery%20close%20relations%20with%20the%20ministry%20of%20defense%20and%20with%20the%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20taking%20on%20dozens%20of%20state%20contracts%2C%20Vyunnyk%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyiv%20has%20ramped%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flithuanian-defense-company-drone-maker-rsi-europe-fpv-ukraine-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrone%3C%2Fa%3E%20production%20since%20Russia%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%2C%20with%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20saying%20in%20October%20that%20Ukraine%20was%20capable%20of%20producing%204%20million%20drones%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20relatively%20cheap%20yet%20highly%20effective%20uncrewed%20systems%20are%20easy%20to%20modify%20and%20can%20be%20used%20for%20a%20range%20of%20missions%2C%20from%20surveillance%20to%20long-range%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthlon%20Avia's%20two%20main%20products%20%E2%80%94%20the%20A1-CM%20Furia%20drone%20and%20the%20ST-35%20Silent%20Thunder%20loitering%20munition%20%E2%80%94%20are%20used%20for%20aerial%20reconnaissance%20and%20precision%20strikes%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAthlon%20says%20the%20catapult-launched%20A1-CM%20has%20a%20range%20of%20up%20to%2050%20km%20(around%2031%20miles)%20and%20has%20been%20used%20for%20reconnaissance%20and%20artillery%20fire%20adjustment%20in%20eastern%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20provided%20the%20system%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20armed%20forces%2C%20the%20National%20Guard%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20the%20Security%20Service%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ST-35%20weapon%20system%20is%20designed%20to%20strike%20targets%20in%20densely%20built%20urban%20areas%20while%20minimizing%20collateral%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20equipped%20with%20a%20number%20of%20different%20warhead%20types%2C%20including%20high%20explosive%2C%20thermobaric%2C%20incendiary%2C%20and%20cumulative%2C%20Athlon%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ST-35%20can%20fly%20for%20up%20to%2060%20minutes%20and%20has%20a%20range%20of%2030%20km%20(around%2019%20miles)%2C%20per%20Athlon's%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVyunnyk%20told%20BI%20that%20Athlon%20carries%20out%20more%20than%20200%20missions%20per%20day%2C%20which%20he%20said%20helps%20the%20company%20build%20on%20its%20experiences%2C%20learn%20what%20it%20does%20well%2C%20and%20identify%20areas%20for%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20speeds%20up%20the%20development%20of%20the%20product%20itself%2C%20company%2C%20and%20troops%20because%20they%20get%20much%20more%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20ahead%2C%20Vyunnyk%20said%20Athlon's%20biggest%20challenge%20would%20be%20supporting%20artillery%20units%2C%20which%20are%20some%20of%20the%20company's%20main%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtillery%20systems%20and%20their%20ranges%20are%20growing%20bigger%2C%20Vyunnyk%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20we%20have%20to%20fly%20longer%20and%20much%20farther%20than%20we%20used%20to%20before%20that%2C%20which%20demands%20quite%20serious%20changes%20in%20the%20system.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVyunnyk%20pointed%20to%20a%20new%20plane%20the%20company%20is%20developing%2C%20which%20he%20said%20had%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Btwo%20times%20bigger%20than%20a%20standard%20Furia%26quot%3B%20to%20accommodate%20the%20need%20for%20more%20batteries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20said%20that%20another%20issue%20facing%20Ukrainian%20drone%20developers%20is%20electronic%20warfare%20systems%2C%20which%20use%20the%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%20to%20disrupt%20certain%20signals%20like%20GPS%20and%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20systems%20are%20one%20of%20the%20main%20defenses%20against%20drones%20and%20have%20become%20increasingly%20important%20on%20the%20battlefield%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrone%20makers%20have%20tried%20to%20adapt%20by%20developing%20frequency-hopping%20solutions%20to%20help%20evade%20such%20defenses%2C%20but%20Vyunnyk%20said%20it%20was%20like%20playing%20a%20game%20of%20cat%20and%20mouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20make%20new%20jamming%20systems%20while%20we%20come%20up%20with%20new%20solutions%20for%20frequency-hopping%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20a%20game%20we%20are%20playing%20with%20our%20enemy.%20Sometimes%20we%20are%20ahead%2C%20sometimes%20we%20are%20not.%20But%20in%20general%2C%20I%20would%20say%20that%20we%20have%20some%20kind%20of%20balance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20holds%20a%20fake%20bomb%20attached%20to%20a%20flying%20drone%20in%20a%20grassy%20field%20with%20a%20blue%20sky%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67378aa6192f52589858e2a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223602%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20with%20a%20drone.%3Cp%3EPaula%20Bronstein%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20efforts%20to%20get%20more%20drones%20to%20the%20front%20lines%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20government%20has%20taken%20a%20number%20of%20steps%20to%20speed%20up%20the%20procurement%20process%20for%20its%20forces%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-russia-drones-procurement-war-uav-conflict-kyiv-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproviding%20additional%20funds%20for%20brigades%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20purchase%20drone%20equipment%20directly%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-launches-new-supply-model-reduces-drone-delivery-to-weeks-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunching%20a%20new%20drone%20supply%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20aimed%20at%20reducing%20delivery%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20efforts%20will%20likely%20have%20come%20as%20welcome%20news%20to%20local%20drone%20manufacturers%20like%20Athlon%20Avia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20early%20days%2C%20nailing%20down%20state%20contracts%20was%20an%20uphill%20battle%2C%20Vyunnyk%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20full-scale%20war%2C%20things%20have%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLegislation%20changed.%20It%20becam