-a642-140a066ee3e9%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20highlight%20achievements%20big%20and%20small%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20just%20had%20a%20big%20win%20at%20work%2C%20consider%20sending%20an%20email%20to%20your%20boss%20about%20it%2C%20or%20bring%20it%20up%20in%20a%20hallway%20conversation%20or%20a%20meeting.%20Wilding%20also%20recommends%20kicking%20off%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-on-one-weekly-meeting-with-boss-mistakes-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregular%20check-ins%20with%20your%20boss%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20recapping%20what%20you%20accomplished%20since%20you%20last%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilding%20said%20to%20talk%20about%20not%20just%20what%20you%20did%2C%20but%20also%20the%20impact%20of%20your%20work%3A%20What%20business%20value%20or%20efficiency%20did%20it%20create%2C%20or%20what%20time%20or%20money%20did%20it%20save%20your%20team%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20approaching%20this%20as%20self-promotion%2C%20think%20of%20it%20as%20simply%20informing%20your%20manager%2C%20so%20they%20can%20communicate%20these%20accomplishments%20and%20outcomes%20up%20their%20own%20chain%20of%20command%20to%20get%20your%20team%20more%20resources%20or%20influence%2C%20Wilding%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20in%20a%20meeting%2C%20you%20might%20bring%20up%20a%20significant%20milestone%20on%20a%20project%20as%20a%20teaching%20moment%20so%20you%20can%20share%20what%20you%20learned%20with%20your%20teammates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20the%20added%20benefit%20of%20giving%20visibility%20into%20how%20you%20process%20information%20and%20make%20decisions%20in%20the%20company's%20best%20interest%2C%20she%20said.%20Showing%20those%20in%20leadership%20your%20higher-level%20thinking%20at%20work%20could%20help%20with%20your%20career%20advancement%20more%20than%20simply%20saying%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkpi-spreadsheet-set-track-marketing-goals-cut-costs-generate-revenue-2020-10%5C%22%20tar